{
  "texts": [
    "Clinically, \"gaming disorder\" foot_8 and depersonalization and derealization dissociative disorders are associated with 2D gaming (De Pasquale et al., 2018; WHO Team, 2020) and could be more prevalent in IXR.",
    "Subclinical \"video game addiction\" can also be harmful (Digital, Culture, Media and Sport Committee, 2019), and readjustment difficulties have been reported when exiting virtual worlds (Michael & Metzinger, 2016; Spiegel, 2018).",
    "Additionally, online games can encourage excessive spending, particularly by children and cognitively disabled users (Kleinman, 2019).",
    "In immersive contexts, AR advertising has been shown to increase customers' willingness to pay (Pozharliev et al., 2022).",
    "An immersive context may also add a sense of \"unreality\" (virtualization or gamification) of financial consequences."
  ]
}